01/09/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Serbia wants to boost political dialogue and strengthen relations with the United States, Prime Minister Mirko Cvetkovic said on Tuesday (August 31st) during talks with a visiting US congressional delegation.
Cvetkovic reaffirmed that Belgrade's strategic goal is EU membership.
Concerning Kosovo, he said his country believes that compromise is possible only through dialogue.
Members of the delegation praised progress Serbia has made in recent years.
While in Belgrade, they also met with President Boris Tadic and Deputy Prime Ministers Mladjan Dinkic and Bozidar Djelic.
(Tanjug, Beta - 31/08/10)
